w%2C%20it's%20said%20that%20if%20you%20park%20at%20the%20site%20of%20the%20crash%2C%20you'll%20hear%20disembodied%20footsteps%20getting%20closer%20and%20closer%20to%20your%20car.%20People%20have%20reported%20handprints%20on%20their%20windows%20and%20banging%20noises%20as%20if%20someone%20was%20kicking%20the%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECONNECTICUT%3A%20Hannah%20Cranna%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222574%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22creepy%20graveyard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f40173789aff80028ab741a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221930%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYou%20can%20visit%20Hannah%20Cranna's%20real%20grave.%3Cp%3EHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKnown%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BWicked%20Witch%20of%20Monroe%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ctinsider.com%2Fconnecticutmagazine%2Farticle%2FThe-CT-Files-Hannah-Cranna-The-Wicked-Witch-of-17041731.php%5C%22%3ECT%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Hannah%20Cranna%20gained%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20witch%20in%20the%2019th%20century%20when%20her%20husband%20died%20by%20mysteriously%20falling%20off%20a%20cliff%20%E2%80%94%20and%20locals%20reportedly%20believed%20that%20she%20had%20bewitched%20him.%20People%20also%20believed%20that%20she%20would%C2%A0cast%20spells%C2%A0on%20people%20she%20didn't%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHannah%20lived%20to%20the%20age%20of%2077%2C%20but%20right%20before%20she%20died%2C%20she%20asked%20to%20be%20carried%20down%20to%20the%20cemetery%20in%20her%20coffin%20by%20foot%2C%20not%20by%20wagon.%20After%20her%20death%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Monroe%20tried%20to%20wheel%20her%20coffin%20down%20the%20hill%20but%20were%20unable%20%E2%80%94%20the%20coffin%20kept%20falling%20off%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they%20were%20forced%20to%20carry%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20townspeople%20returned%20to%20her%20home%2C%20it%20was%20found%20to%20be%20engulfed%20in%20flames%2C%20sealing%20Hannah's%20reputation%20for%20practicing%20witchcraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20you%20can%20visit%20her%20real%20grave%20in%20Trumbull.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDELAWARE%3A%20The%20ghost%20of%20Mr.%20Chew%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22delaware%20courthouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f4017e742f43f001ddfe68e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20home%20of%20Mr.%20Chew%20in%20Dover.%3Cp%3ERosemarie%20Mosteller%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20not%20a%20particularly%20mean-spirited%20ghost%2C%20Samuel%20Chew's%20story%2C%20as%20told%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Diim03Qp4kaIC%26pg%3DPA23%26lpg%3DPA23%26dq%3Dmr.%2Bchew%2Bdelaware%26source%3Dbl%26ots%3Das70HXp2Ln%26sig%3DyWKCk1gGTvLQXBEUDFbW7WIZQQA%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D0ahUKEwi7gIfBzL7YAhWGk-AKHX73AqsQ6AEIYTAO%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Dmr.%2520chew%2520delaware%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BHaunted%20Delaware%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20still%20disconcerting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChew%20was%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Delaware%20Supreme%20Court%20in%201741.%20As%20the%20story%20goes%2C%20while%20he%20was%20alive%2C%20he%20didn't%20always%20get%20the%20respect%20he%20deserved%20%E2%80%94%20people%20frequently%20made%20fun%20of%20his%20name%20by%20mimicking%20sneezes%20while%20he%20walked%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20death%2C%20people%20reported%20seeing%20his%20ghost%20sitting%20under%20a%20poplar%20tree%2C%20wandering%20the%20courthouse%2C%20and%20generally%20creeping%20out%20the%20residents%20of%20Dover.%20Chew%20would%20also%20pull%20on%20men's%20coattails%20and%20give%20women%20a%20cold%2C%20icy%20feeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFLORIDA%3A%20The%20gravity-defying%20Spook%20Hill%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221422%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22spook%20hilll%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f40183a42f43f001ddfe693%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20sign%20explains%20the%20story%20of%20the%20popular%20attraction.%3Cp%3EInspired%20By%20Maps%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phenomenon%20that%20happens%20at%20Spook%20Hill%20is%20real%3A%20Cars%20that%20are%20parked%20in%20neutral%20will%20appear%20to%20roll%20uphill%2C%20according%20to%C2%A0Atlas%20Obscura.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegends%20say%20the%20hill%20is%20either%20the%20site%20of%20a%20Native%20American%20burial%20ground%20or%20an%20epic%20battle%20of%20a%20Native%20American%20chief%20against%20a%20crocodile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20truth%20is%20it's%20actually%20just%20an%20illusion%20created%20by%20the%20hill's%20surroundings.%20While%20cars%20appear%20to%20be%20rolling%20uphill%2C%20they%20are%20still%20just%20rolling%20downhill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EGEORGIA%3A%20The%20ghost%20town%20of%20Lake%20Lanier%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221869%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lake%20lanier%20georgia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f4018c842f43f001ddfe69f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221402%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELake%20Lanier%20is%20the%20largest%20man-made%20lake%20in%20Georgia.%3Cp%3ERodClementPhotography%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20bottom%20of%20Lake%20Lanier%20lies%20(almost)%20fully%20intact%20towns%2C%20ferries%2C%20a%20racetrack%2C%20and%20multiple%20cemeteries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201946%2C%20the%20Georgia%20government%20received%20congressional%20approval%20to%20create%20Lake%20Lanier%2C%20and%20it%20bought%20up%20entire%20towns%20to%20clear%20the%20space%20for%20the%20lake.%20However%2C%20it%20decided%20to%20let%20the%20water%20cover%20the%20towns%20rather%20than%20demolish%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Lake%20Lanier%20has%20a%20decidedly%20eerie%20feel%20about%20it.%20There%20have%20been%20an%20unusual%20number%20of%20freak%20accidents%20and%20deaths%20on%20the%20lake.%20From%201994%20to%202020%2C%20there%20were%20203%20drownings%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2020%2F10%2F31%2Fus%2Flake-lanier-urban-legends-trnd%2Findex.html%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20bodies%20of%20people%20who%20drowned%20have%20never%20been%20recovered.%20People%20have%20reported%20feeling%20arms%20and%20legs%20in%20the%20water%2C%20reported%20CNN%2C%20but%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20find%20them%20right%20after%2C%20leading%20people%20to%20believe%20that%20spirits%20still%20roam%20the%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHAWAII%3A%20Night%20Marchers%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222449%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22christmas%20bonfire%20louisiana%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d7ffe1a6f24eb4ba2099745%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221837%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYou%20know%20a%20night%20march%20is%20coming%20when%20you%20see%20the%20torches%20and%20hear%20the%20drums.%3Cp%3EEthan%20Miller%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENight%20Marchers%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.honolulumagazine.com%2FHonolulu-Magazine%2FOctober-2014%2FFriday-Frights-The-Legend-of-Hawaiis-Night-Marchers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHonolulu%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20not%20evil%20spirits%2C%20but%20they%20do%20demand%20respect.%20They%20are%20spirits%20of%20ancient%20Hawaiian%20warriors%20who%20marched%20around%20the%20islands%20to%20protect%20sacred%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegend%20says%20that%20if%20you%20look%20directly%20at%20a%20night%20marcher%2C%20you%20will%20be%20marked%20for%20death.%20And%2C%20if%20by%20some%20chance%2C%20you%20find%20yourself%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20procession%2C%20you%20are%20supposed%20to%20lie%20down%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIDAHO%3A%20The%20water%20babies%20of%20Massacre%20Rocks%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222180%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22massacre%20rocks%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f40194b89aff80028ab7434%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221635%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20water%20babies%20can%20be%20found%20in%20Massacre%20Rocks%20State%20Park.%3Cp%3EZack%20Frank%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWater%20babies%20are%20a%20Native%20American%20legend%20found%20in%20several%20places%20in%20America%2C%20most%20famously%20in%20Pocatello%20at%20Massacre%20Rocks%20State%20Park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Shoshone%20tribe%20was%20first%20recorded%20in%201805%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fplainshumanities.unl.edu%2Fencyclopedia%2Fdoc%2Fegp.na.105%5C%22%3EEncyclopedia%20of%20the%20Great%20Plains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20was%20roaming%20the%20Great%20Plains%20as%20early%20as%20the%201500s%2C%20so%20it's%20not%20clear%20when%20exactly%20this%20legend%20originated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20story%20goes%20that%20the%20Shoshone%20experienced%20an%20extreme%20famine%2C%20and%20mothers%20were%20forced%20to%20drown%20their%20babies%20in%20the%20river%20rather%20than%20watch%20their%20children%20starve%2C%20as%20told%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onlyinyourstate.com%2Fnature%2Fidaho%2Fmassacre-rocks-id%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOnly%20In%20Your%20State.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20some%20people%20claim%20that%20if%20you%20sit%20quietly%20at%20the%20river%20by%20Massacre%20Rocks%2C%20you'll%20hear%20the%20sound%20of%20babies%20crying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20stories%20say%20that%20these%20babies%20grew%20gills%20and%20fins%20and%20survived%2C%20and%20now%20they%20seek%20revenge%20on%20their%20mothers%20by%20luring%20unsuspecting%20victims%20to%20their%20deaths%20in%20the%20river.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EILLINOIS%3A%20Homey%20the%20Clown%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223177%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22bozo%20the%20clown%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d7ffe876f24eb4bc4297233%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222383%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClowns%20are%20undoubtedly%20creepy.%3Cp%3EHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Chicago%20in%20the%20'90s%2C%20there%20was%20a%20rumor%20going%20around%20elementary%20schools%3A%20There%20was%20a%20creepy%20man%20dressed%20as%20Homey%20the%20Clown%20(yes%2C%20from%20%26quot%3BIn%20Living%20Color%26quot%3B)%2C%20driving%20around%20in%20a%20white%20van%20trying%20to%20lure%20kids%20into%20it%20with%20candy%20and%20money%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchicagoreader.com%2Fnews-politics%2Furban-legends-who-saw-homey-the-clown%2F%5C%22%3EChicago%20Reader%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagotribune.com%2Fnews%2Fct-xpm-1991-10-11-9104010895-story.html%5C%22%3EThe%20Chicago%20Tribune.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20variations%2C%20he%20was%20a%20kidnapper%3B%20in%20others%2C%20he%20was%20a%20rapist.%20But%20in%20all%20variations%2C%20Homey%20left%20a%20mark%20on%20young%20Chicago%20kids%20in%20the%20'90s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EINDIANA%3A%20The%20100%20Steps%20Cemetery%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cemetery%20night%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a4e5ddd3639201a008b4580%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cemetery%20is%20located%20in%20Brazil%2C%20Indiana.%3Cp%3EThomas%20Zsebok%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20100%20Steps%20Cemetery%20is%20located%20in%20Brazil.%20While%20it's%20unclear%20when%20the%20stories%20about%20the%20cemetery%20being%20haunted%20began%2C%20some%20gravestones%20date%20back%20to%20the%201860s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legend%20states%20that%20if%20someone%20finds%20themselves%20in%20the%20cemetery%20at%20midnight%2C%20they%20must%20climb%20the%20steps%20and%20count%20to%20100.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20a%20ghost%20of%20an%20undertaker%20will%20appear%20and%20show%20the%20person%20a%20vision%20of%20their%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20way%20back%20down%2C%20the%20visitor%20is%20supposed%20to%20count%20the%20steps%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eagain%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eif%20they%20count%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20steps%2C%20the%20vision%20is%20false.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20have%20visited%20the%20cemetery%20in%20the%20past%20have%20tried%20to%20outsmart%20the%20supernatural%20forces%20in%20100%20Steps%20by%20avoiding%20the%20steps%20altogether.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Findianaghostdetectives.blogspot.com%2F2014%2F05%2F100-step-cemetery-brazil-indiana.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndiana%20Ghost%20Detectives%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20they've%20reported%20being%20knocked%20or%20shoved%20to%20the%20ground%20by%20an%20unseen%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIOWA%3A%20The%20Black%20Angel%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22black%20angel%20iowa%20city%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f401a3089aff80028ab7439%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShe's%20located%20in%20Oakland%20Cemetery.%3Cp%3EIN%20Dancing%20Light%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Black%20Angel%20stands%20over%208%20feet%20tall%20in%20Oakland%20Cemetery%20in%20Iowa%20City%2C%20and%20she%20is%20black%20due%20to%20oxidation.%20According%20to%20Atlas%20Obscura%2C%20multiple%20legends%20have%20cropped%20up%20around%20her%2C%20most%20likely%20because%20of%20her%20dark%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20legend%20says%20that%20a%C2%A0pregnant%20woman%20should%20never%20walk%20under%20her%2C%20or%20she'll%20lose%20the%20child.%20Others%20say%20that%20if%20you%20touch%20or%20kiss%20the%20statue%2C%20you'll%20be%20dead%20within%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20haunted%2C%20cursed%2C%20or%20completely%20harmless%2C%20the%20statue%20is%20definitely%20a%20somber%20sight%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EKANSAS%3A%20The%20Devil's%20Chair%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cemetery%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5babca251f933e0ab43fe563%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20chair%20is%20located%20in%20Alma%20Cemetery.%3Cp%3Esonnee101%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Only%20In%20Your%20State%2C%20the%20legend%20of%20the%20Devil's%20Chair%20goes%20like%20this%3A%20An%20old%20farmer%20in%20Alma%20refused%20to%20sell%20his%20land%20to%20the%20city%20in%20order%20to%20build%20a%20new%20cemetery.%20Someone%20got%20a%20little%20too%20tired%20of%20waiting%20for%20him%20to%20sell%2C%20so%20he%20was%20pushed%20into%20his%20own%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20someone%20said%20that%20there%20was%20a%20terrible%20smell%20coming%20from%20the%20well%2C%20so%20the%20city%20sent%20someone%20to%20investigate.%20It%20was%20ruled%20that%20the%20well%20was%20empty%2C%20and%20it%20was%20boarded%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20if%20you%20make%20your%20way%20to%20Alma%2C%20you%20can%20actually%20sit%20on%20the%20boarded-up%20well%2C%20but%20legend%20says%20that%20people%20who%20have%20sat%20on%20the%20well%20have%20been%20known%20to%20mysteriously%20disappear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EKENTUCKY%3A%20The%20Goat%20Man%20of%20Pope%20Lick%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223721%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22pope%20lick%20bridge%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f401df642f43f001ddfe6c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222790%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHe's%20been%20spotted%20underneath%20this%20trestle.%3Cp%3EMichele%20Korfhage%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20clear%20consensus%20on%20how%20the%20Goat%20Man%20came%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20some%20say%20he%20was%20a%20circus%20performer%3B%20others%20say%20he%20was%20a%20farmer%20who%20tortured%20his%20goats%20for%20Satan%20and%2C%20in%20return%2C%20was%20transformed%20into%20a%20hideous%20goat%20monster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20everyone%20does%20agree%20on%20his%20appearance%3A%20dark%20fur%2C%20pale%20skin%2C%20goat%20legs%2C%20and%20horns%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wave3.com%2Fstory%2F25479436%2Fnumerous-urban-legends-tell-of-louisvilles-goat-man%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWave3%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20local%20news%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20monster%20is%20said%20to%20hide%20under%20the%20bridge%20at%20Pope%20Lick%20Creek%20in%20Louisville%20to%20lure%20people%20onto%20the%20train%20tracks%2C%20only%20to%20see%20them%20be%20hit%20by%20oncoming%20trains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESadly%2C%20this%20urban%20legend%20has%20had%20some%20dangerous%20consequences.%20In%202016%2C%20an%20Ohio%20woman%20fell%20to%20her%20death%20from%20the%20bridge%20while%20looking%20for%20the%20Goat%20Man%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnews%2Fmorning-mix%2Fwp%2F2016%2F04%2F26%2Fcouples-curiosity-about-kentuckys-goatman-legend-takes-fatal-turn-on-railroad-trestle%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELOUISIANA%3A%20The%20Grunch%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223554%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22swamp%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f43e09889aff80028ab77c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Grunch%20make%20their%20home%20in%20East%20New%20Orleans.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FBeth%20J.%20Harpaz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGrunch%20Road%20is%20an%20old%20dirt%20road%20that%20leads%20deep%20into%20the%20woods%20and%20eventually%20to%20a%20dead%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20favorite%20place%20for%20teenagers%20to%20go%20and%20do%20whatever%20teenagers%20do%20until%20they%20learned%20about%20the%20Grunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexemplore.com%2Fparanormal%2FLouisiana-Edition-Urban-Legends-Monsters-And-Haunted-Places-The-Series%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHubPages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Grunch%20are%20rumored%20to%20be%20a%20group%20of%20deformed%2C%20half-human%2C%20half-monsters%20that%20resulted%20from%20years%20of%20isolation%20in%20the%20Louisiana%20Bayous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20present%20day%2C%20it's%20said%20that%20if%20you%20find%20yourself%20on%20Grunch%20Road%2C%20don't%20get%20out%20of%20your%20car%20if%20you%20see%20a%20goat%20who%20looks%20injured.%20The%20stories%20say%20that%20the%20Grunch%20uses%20goats%20to%20lure%20people%20out%20of%20their%20cars%20so%20they%20can%20eat%20them%20and%20drain%20their%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMAINE%3A%20The%20mysterious%20stain%20on%20Colonel%20Jonathan%20Buck's%20tomb%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22946%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22bucksport%20maine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f40273042f43f001ddfe6ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22710%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBuck's%20tomb%20is%20in%20the%20town%20bearing%20his%20name%3A%20Bucksport.%3Cp%3EESB%20Essentials%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tomb%20of%20Colonel%20Jonathan%20Buck%20in%20Bucksport%20bears%20a%20mysterious%20leg-shaped%20stain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20goes%20that%20Buck%20sentenced%20a%20woman%20to%20burn%20for%20witchcraft%2C%20and%20while%20she%20was%20burning%2C%20her%20leg%20rolled%20out%20of%20the%20fire.%20It's%20also%20been%20said%20that%20the%20witch%20cursed%20Buck's%20tomb%20to%20always%20bear%20a%20stain%20for%20this%20injustice%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bangordailynews.com%2F2015%2F10%2F28%2Fliving%2Fa-close-look-at-the-legend-of-jonathan-buck%2F%5C%22%3EBangor%20Daily%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20said%20that%20people%20have%20tried%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20this%20stain%20twice%2C%20but%20the%20stain%20keeps%20reappearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMARYLAND%3A%20Chessie%20the%20Chesapeake%20Bay%20monster%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22chesapeak%20bay%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a4e73bb4931461c008b4573%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDoes%20a%20sea%20monster%20really%20live%20in%20the%20Chesapeake%20Bay%3F%3Cp%3EJon%20Bilous%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChessie%20sightings%20have%20been%20around%20since%20the%201930s%20but%20really%20started%20to%20pick%20up%20steam%20in%20the%20'80s%20when%20photographic%20evidence%20became%20more%20readily%20available%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wbaltv.com%2Farticle%2Flegend-of-chessie-alive-well-in-maryland%2F13126354%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWBAL-TV%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChessie%20is%20said%20to%20resemble%20a%20snake%2C%20measures%20around%2030%20feet%20long%2C%20and%20is%20the%20approximate%20thickness%20of%20a%20telephone%20pole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20haven't%20been%20any%20recorded%20attacks%20from%20Chessie%2C%20but%20a%2030-foot-long%20snake%20does%20not%20sound%20like%20something%20most%20people%20would%20want%20to%20run%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMASSACHUSETTS%3A%20The%20spirits%20of%20Hoosac%20Tunnel%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221314%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hoosac%20tunnel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f40279289aff80028ab74a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22986%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20tunnel%20took%2024%20years%20to%20complete.%3Cp%3EMorphart%20Creation%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2024-year-long%20construction%20of%20the%20Hoosac%20Tunnel%20in%20western%20Massachusetts%2C%20about%20200%20men%20died.%20Death%20was%20so%20associated%20with%20the%20tunnel%20that%20it%20was%20actually%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BThe%20Bloody%20Pit%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Atlas%20Obscura.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20particularly%20gruesome%20explosion%20in%20either%201867%20or%201868%2C%2013%20miners%20were%20trapped%20inside%20the%20tunnel.%20The%20other%20workers%20assumed%20that%20the%20miners%20had%20died%2C%20but%20eventually%2C%20it%20was%20discovered%20the%20miners%20had%20lived%2C%20built%20a%20raft%20to%20combat%20flooding%2C%20and%20eventually%20died%20due%20to%20poisonous%20gas%20inhalation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20said%20that%20these%2013%20miners%20haunted%20the%20tunnel%20for%20years%2C%20moaning%20and%20briefly%20appearing%20as%20ghosts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMICHIGAN%3A%20The%20little%20girl%20on%20Knock%20Knock%20Road%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223797%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22dark%20road%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a4f99ac493146a30d8b4577%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222848%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20road's%20real%20name%20is%20Strasburg%20Road%2C%20located%20in%20Grosse%20Ile.%3Cp%3EIlkin%20Zeferli%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legend%20of%20Knock%20Knock%20Road%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F99wfmk.com%2Fknockknockroad%2F%5C%22%3E99.1%20WMFK%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20that%20there%20was%20a%20little%20girl%20who%20was%20murdered%20on%20Knock%20Knock%20Road%20in%20the%20Detroit%20area%2C%20and%20now%20she%20appears%20to%20drivers%20at%20their%20car%20window%2C%20knocking%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20person%20who%20killed%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMINNESOTA%3A%20The%20Kensington%20runestone%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kensington%20rune%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f40280589aff80028ab74ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20stone%20is%20displayed%20in%20Alexandria%2C%20Minnesota.%3Cp%3EJames%20Kirkikis%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201898%2C%20a%20Swedish-American%20farmer%20found%20a%20gigantic%20slab%20of%20rock%20on%20his%20farm%20with%20symbols%20that%20appeared%20to%20be%20Norse.%20Since%20then%2C%20no%20one%20has%20figured%20out%20where%20it%20came%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20historians%20have%20debunked%20the%20rock%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20now%20known%20as%20the%20Kensington%20Rune%2C%20according%20to%20Atlas%20Obscura%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20hoax%2C%20due%20to%20dating%20and%20inconsistencies%20with%20the%20Norse%20language%20of%20the%20time%2C%20the%20myth%20has%20persisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20it%20wasn't%20the%20Vikings%2C%20who%20did%20leave%20this%20mysterious%20rock%3F%20And%20what%20does%20it%20say%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMISSISSIPPI%3A%20Deer%20Island's%20haunted%20treasure%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222844%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22creepy%20islsand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a4f9e774931461f008b4591%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222133%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDeer%20Island%20is%20just%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Mississippi.%3Cp%3EAlexey%20Stiop%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ghost%20of%20Deer%20Island%2C%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sunherald.com%2Fliving%2Farticle39639327.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESun-Herald%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20originates%20from%20an%20old%20pirate%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20says%20that%20back%20in%20the%201920s%2C%20two%20men%20were%20fishing%20on%20Deer%20Island%20when%20they%20heard%20rustling%20in%20the%20bushes%2C%20a%20noise%20they%20assumed%20was%20caused%20by%20wild%20hogs.%20Eventually%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20check%20it%20out%20and%20encountered%20a%20headless%20skeleton.%20They%20ran%20back%20to%20their%20boat%2C%20and%20the%20skeleton%20followed%20them%20all%20the%20way%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20pirates'%20story%2C%20there%20was%20a%20ship%20that%20sailed%20into%20Biloxi%20Bay%20and%20buried%20their%20treasure%20on%20Deer%20Island.%20The%20crew%20decided%20to%20behead%20one%20of%20their%20own%20and%20left%20his%20body%20behind%20to%20guard%20their%20treasure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMISSOURI%3A%20Momo%20the%20Missouri%20Monster%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224992%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22yeti%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d80f5cf6f24eb002d0670d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMomo%20was%20first%20spotted%20in%20Louisiana%2C%20and%20then%20moved%20north.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMomo%20is%20Missouri's%20version%20of%20Bigfoot%2FSasquatch.%20He's%20been%20said%20to%20have%20terrible%20body%20odor%2C%20a%20pumpkin-shaped%20head%2C%20and%20an%20appetite%20for%20dogs.%20In%201968%2C%20Momo%20tried%20to%20abduct%20a%204-year-old%20boy%2C%20though%20no%20evidence%20was%20ever%20found%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F101theeagle.com%2Fthe-legend-of-momo-the-missouri-monster%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20local%20radio%20station%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMONTANA%3A%20The%20story%20of%20Sacrifice%20Cliff%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221809%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22sacrifice%20cliffs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f4028b642f43f001ddfe70c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221357%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESacrifice%20Cliff%20looks%20over%20Billings.%3Cp%3EKPV89%2FShutterstock%