n%20Shortlisted%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Aeronautics%20Space%20Agency%20(NASA)%20shortlisted%20nine%20potential%20landing%20sites%20near%20the%20lunar%20South%20Pole%20for%20its%20upcoming%20Artemis%20III%20mission.%20This%20is%20the%20American%20space%20agency's%20first%20crewed%20Moon%20landing%20in%20over%2050%20years.%20These%20locations%20are%20set%20to%20undergo%20thorough%20scientific%20and%20engineering%20assessments%2C%20and%20NASA%20plans%20to%20continue%20exploring%20other%20areas%20for%20future%20missions%20beyond%20this%20selection.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EThe%20nine%20proposed%20lunar%20landing%20regions%20situated%20near%20the%20South%20Pole%20are%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPeak%20near%20Cabeus%20B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHaworth%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMalapert%20Massif%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMons%20Mouton%20Plateau%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMons%20Mouton%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENobile%20Rim%201%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENobile%20Rim%202%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Ede%20Gerlache%20Rim%202%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESlater%20Plain%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NASA%2C%20each%20of%20these%20nine%20locations%20offers%20the%20chance%20to%20gain%20vital%20information%20about%20rocky%20planets%2C%20lunar%20resources%20and%20the%20broader%20history%20of%20the%20solar%20system.%20Unexplored%20by%20crewed%20missions%2C%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole%20has%20permanently%20dark%20regions%20that%20may%20contain%20essential%20resources%20like%20water.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnLakiesha%20Hawkins%2C%20assistant%20deputy%20associate%20administrator%2C%20Moon%20to%20Mars%20Program%20Office%2C%20NASA%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CArtemis%20will%20return%20humanity%20to%20the%20Moon%20and%20visit%20unexplored%20areas.%20NASA's%20selection%20of%20these%20regions%20shows%20our%20commitment%20to%20landing%20crew%20safely%20near%20the%20lunar%20South%20Pole%2C%20where%20they%20will%20help%20uncover%20new%20scientific%20discoveries%20and%20learn%20to%20live%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnSarah%20Noble%2C%20the%20Artemis%20lunar%20science%20lead%20at%20NASA%20Headquarters%20in%20Washington%20said%20that%20the%20Moon's%20South%20Pole%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccompletely%20different%20environment%E2%80%9D%20than%20where%20the%20landing%20happened%20during%20the%20Apollo%20missions.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20offers%20access%20to%20some%20of%20the%20Moon's%20oldest%20terrain%2C%20as%20well%20as%20cold%2C%20shadowed%20regions%20that%20may%20contain%20water%20and%20other%20compounds%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Noble.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnTo%20determine%20these%20sites%2C%20a%20multidisciplinary%20team%20of%20scientists%20and%20engineers%20analysed%20the%20lunar%20South%20Pole%2C%20leveraging%20data%20from%20NASA's%20Lunar%20Reconnaissance%20Orbiter%20alongside%20extensive%20lunar%20science%20research.%20Key%20considerations%20in%20their%20assessment%20included%20scientific%20potential%2C%20launch%20window%20availability%2C%20terrain%20suitability%2C%20communication%20links%20with%20Earth%2C%20and%20lighting%20conditions.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CArtemis%20III%20will%20be%20the%20first%20time%20that%20astronauts%20will%20land%20in%20the%20south%20polar%20region%20of%20the%20Moon%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Jacob%20Bleacher%2C%20NASA's%20chief%20exploration%20scientist.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20final%20selection%20of%20specific%20landing%20sites%20for%20Artemis%20III%20will%20occur%20after%20NASA%20finalises%20the%20mission's%20launch%20dates%2C%20which%20will%20influence%20transfer%20trajectories%20and%20the%20conditions%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730377560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fmjpmgfa4_artemis-iii_625x300_31_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-identifies-9-potential-landing-sites-for-artemis-iii-mission-near-moon-s-south-pole-6915265%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22N